Benin Says China Civil to Spend $10 Billion on Roads, Railway

-- B y   S e r g e - D a v i d   Z o u e m e
-- 
2011-09-13T14:07:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/benin-says-china-civil-to-spend-10-billion-on-roads-railway.html
China Civil Engineering
Construction Corp. will spend more than $10 billion to build
roads and extend a railway in  Benin , Eugene Dossoumou, the West
African nation’s secretary-general, said in a speech broadcast
on ORTB.  A group of officials from the company met Benin’s
president, Thomas Boni Yayi, yesterday, Dossoumou said on the
Cotonou-based, state-owned broadcaster.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Serge-David Zoueme in Cotonou via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 